# winflation.eu — Project Conventions

> Full context lives in `AGENTS.md` (project root). Read it when deeper detail is needed.

## Tech Stack
- **Vue 3** (`<script setup>` + Composition API)
- **TypeScript** (strict mode)
- **Pinia 3** (Setup Store style, `defineStore`)
- **Vue Router 5** (client-side)
- **Tailwind CSS 4** (utility-first, no inline styles)
- **vue-i18n 11** (`useI18n`, no hardcoded strings in templates)
- **Chart.js 4** (line + bar charts)
- **FontAwesome 7** (`<FontAwesomeIcon>` global component)
- **Firebase** (Auth + Firestore, no Storage)
- **Google Gemini** (`gemini-flash-latest`)
- **Yahoo Finance** (`yahoo-finance2`, server-side scripts only)

## Folder Structure
```
src/
  modules/          # Feature modules (DDD)
    <feature>/
      api/          # HTTP requests
      domain/       # TypeScript types
      store/        # Pinia stores
      <feature>.vue
      <feature>.routes.ts
  i18n/locales/     # en-US.ts and pt-BR.ts (always keep in sync)
  plugins/          # firebase.ts, fontawesome.ts
  router/index.ts   # spreads each module's routes
  assets/styles/    # Tailwind entry point
scripts/            # Node maintenance scripts (run from project root)
```

## Conventions
- No `components/` folder at `src/` root — components belong inside their feature module
- Each feature module owns its routes (`<feature>.routes.ts`)
- TypeScript contracts go in `domain/`; Pinia stores in `store/`
- All UI text via `useI18n` — add keys to **both** `en-US.ts` and `pt-BR.ts`
- Icons: register in `src/plugins/fontawesome.ts` before use
- Per-user Firestore data: `users/{uid}` doc with `setDoc({ merge: true })`
- Scripts need `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` + `GEMINI_API_KEY` env vars; run with `node --env-file=.env.local scripts/<name>.mjs`

## Design Rules
- **Never change design/layout unless explicitly asked** — structural refactors (extract component, add store) must preserve the existing markup 1:1
- Every interactive element must have `cursor-pointer`
- Dark mode via Tailwind `dark:` variants — no separate theme files
